  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F).",
    "In a small bowl, mix together goose fat, coconut oil, garlic, ginger, chili peppers, fennel seeds, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Pour the mixture into a 4-6 ramekins, depending on their size.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes, or until the fat has melted and is golden brown.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool slightly.",
    "Crack an egg into each ramekin and sprinkle with palm sugar if desired.",
    "Return to the oven and bake for an additional 10-12 minutes, or until the egg whites are set and the yolks are still runny.",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro if desired.",
    "Serve immediately, with toasted bread or crackers on the side.",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
  ],
